Usage: hh_client check [OPTION]... [WWW-ROOT]

WWW-ROOT is assumed to be current directory if unspecified

  --allow-non-opt-build                                   Override build mode check triggered by warn_on_non_opt_build .hhconfig option
  --autostart-server                                      automatically start hh_server if it's not running (default: true)
  --config                                                override arbitrary value from hh.conf and .hhconfig (format: <key>=<value>)
  --cst-search                                            (mode) Search the concrete syntax trees of files in the codebase for a given pattern
  --cst-search-files                                      Run CST search on this set of files, rather than all the files in the codebase.
  --custom-hhi-path                                       use custom hhi files
  --custom-telemetry-data Add                             a custom column to all logged telemetry samples (format: <column>=<value>)
  --deps-out-at-pos-batch                                 (mode) for each entry in input list get list of what it depends on [file:line:character list]
  --deps-in-at-pos-batch                                  (mode) for each entry in input list get list of what depends on it [file:line:character list]
  --dump-config                                           Output configuration
  --error-format <extended|raw|context|highlighted|plain> Error formatting style; (default: highlighted)
  --file-dependents                                       (mode) Given a list of filepaths, shows list of (possibly) dependent files
  --find-class-refs                                       (mode) finds references of the provided class name
  --find-refs                                             (mode) finds references of the provided symbol; optionally specify the symbol kind like "Kind|Symbol" (looks for functions or methods if unspecified); valid kinds are Method, Property, Class_const, Typeconst, Function, Class, ExplicitClass, and GConst; use ExplicitClass instead of Class to exclude references via self/static/parent
  --find-my-tests                                         (deprecated, use --find-my-tests-v1) return test files that reference the given methods [C::m list]
  --find-my-tests-v1                                      (mode) return test files that reference the given methods [C::m list]
  --find-my-tests-staging                                 (mode) return test files that reference the given symbols, using the staging implementation
  --find-my-tests-max-distance maximum                    distance between given symbol(s) and any test that --find-my-tests will return (default: 1)
  --find-my-tests-max-test-files maximum                  number of test files to return from --find-my-tests (default: unlimited)
  --force-dormant-start                                   If server is dormant, force start a new one instead of waiting for the next one to start up automatically (default: false)
  --from                                                  so we know who's calling hh_client - e.g. nuclide, vim, emacs, vscode
  --from-arc-diff                                         (deprecated) equivalent to --from arc_diff
  --from-arc-land                                         (deprecated) equivalent to --from arc_land
  --from-check-trunk                                      (deprecated) equivalent to --from check_trunk
  --from-emacs                                            (deprecated) equivalent to --from emacs
  --from-vim                                              (deprecated) equivalent to --from vim
  --fun-deps-at-pos-batch                                 (mode) for each entry in input list get list of function dependencies [file:line:character list]
  --go-to-impl-class                                      (mode) goes to implementation of the provided class/trait/interface/etc. with the given name
  --go-to-impl-method                                     (mode) goes to implementation of the provided method name
  --hack-to-notebook Convert                              a Hack file generated by `hh --notebook-to-hack` into a notebook. Pass hack file contents via stdin
  --ide-find-refs-by-symbol (mode)                        similar to IDE_FIND_REFS, but takes a symbol name rather than position
  --ide-find-refs-by-symbol3 (mode)                       similar to FIND_REFS, but takes [action stream_file hints]
  --ide-go-to-impl-by-symbol (mode)                       similar to IDE_GO_TO_IMPL, but takes a symbol name rather than position
  --ide-rename-by-symbol                                  (mode) renames, but takes a Find_refs.action. Usage: hh_client <new name>|<comma_separated_action>
  --identify-function                                     (mode) print the full function name at the position [line:character] of the text on stdin
  --identify                                              (mode) identify the named symbol
  --ignore-hh-version                                     ignore hh_version check when loading saved states (default: false)
  --in-memory-dep-table-size                              number of entries in the in-memory dependency table
  --inheritance-ancestor-classes                          (mode) prints a list of classes that this class extends
  --inheritance-ancestor-classes-batch                    (mode) prints a list of classes that these classes extend
  --inheritance-ancestor-interfaces                       (mode) prints a list of interfaces that this class implements
  --inheritance-ancestor-interfaces-batch                 (mode) prints a list of interfaces that these classes implement
  --inheritance-ancestor-traits                           (mode) prints a list of traits that this class uses
  --inheritance-ancestor-traits-batch                     (mode) prints a list of traits that these classes use
  --inheritance-ancestors                                 (mode) prints a list of all related classes or methods to the given class
  --inheritance-children                                  (mode) prints a list of all related classes or methods to the given class
  --json                                                  output json for machine consumption (default: false)
  --jsonl                                                 output streaming jsonl (JSON Lines) for machine consumption (default: false)
  --lint                                                  (mode) lint the given list of files
  --lint-all                                              (mode) find all occurrences of lint with the given error code
  --lint-stdin                                            (mode) lint a file given on stdin; the filename should be the argument to this option
  --list-files                                            (mode) list files with errors
  --lock-file                                             (mode) show lock file name and exit
  --max-errors                                            Maximum number of errors to display
  --preexisting-warnings                                  show all preexisting warnings in typechecked files (default: false)
  --logname                                               (mode) show log filename and exit
  --monitor-logname                                       (mode) show monitor log filename and exit
  --client-logname                                        (mode) show client log filename and exit
  --ide-logname                                           (mode) show client ide log filename and exit
  --lsp-logname                                           (mode) show client lsp log filename and exit
  --no-load                                               start from a fresh state
  --notebook-to-hack Convert                              notebook to a Hack file. Arg: notebook_number (example: "N12345"). Pass notebook in .ipynb format to stdin and a header (such as a copyright notice comment)
  --outline                                               (mode) prints an outline of the text on stdin
  --package-lint Support                                  for linting of __PackageOverride annotations
  --prechecked                                            override value of "prechecked_files" flag from hh.conf
  --no-prechecked                                         override value of "prechecked_files" flag from hh.conf
  --with-mini-state                                       Init with the given saved state instead of the one based on current repo version.
  --profile-log                                           enable profile logging
  --refactor                                              (mode) rename a symbol, Usage: hh_client ["Class", "Function", "Method"] <Current Name> <New Name>
  --remove-dead-fixme                                     (mode) remove dead HH_FIXME for specified error code (first do hh_client restart --no-load)
  --remove-dead-fixmes                                    (mode) remove dead HH_FIXME for any error code < 5000 (first do hh_client restart --no-load)
  --remove-dead-unsafe-casts                              (mode) remove dead UNSAFE_CASTS (first do hh_client restart --no-load)
  --retries                                               (deprecated) same as --timeout
  --retry-if-init                                         (deprecated and ignored)
  --rewrite-declarations Rewrite                          Hack source code allowed in notebooks to valid Hack.
For example in `function foo(): void {} function foo(): void{}` we
rewrite to the function names to something like `foo_1` and `foo_2`.

  --rewrite-lambda-parameters                             (mode) rewrite lambdas in the files from the given list with suggested parameter types
  --save-naming                                           (mode) Save the naming table to the given file. Returns the number of files and symbols written to disk.
  --save-64bit                                            save discovered 64-bit to the given directory
  --save-human-readable-64bit-dep-map                     save map of 64bit hashes to names to files in the given directory
  --saved-state-ignore-hhconfig                           ignore hhconfig hash when loading saved states (default: false)
  --search                                                (mode) --search this_is_just_to_check_liveness_of_hh_server
  --server-rage                                           (mode) dumps internal state of hh_server
  --show-spinner                                          shows a spinner while awaiting the typechecker
  --single <path>                                         Return errors in file with provided name (give '-' for stdin)
  --multi <path>                                          Return errors for files read from the given file (one per line)
  --log-errors                                            (mode) type check the given list of files and log their errors (use --log-to-file to specify output file)
  --log-to-file <path>                                    Write logged errors to specified file (use with --log-errors)
  --show-tast                                             in combination with `--single`, output the TASTs of the file along with TAST hashes.
  --sort-results                                          sort output for CST search.
  --stats                                                 display some server statistics
  --stdin-name                                            substitute stdin for contents of file with specified name
  --status                                                (mode) show a human readable list of errors (default)
  --timeout                                               set the timeout in seconds (default: no timeout)
  --type-at-pos                                           (mode) show type at a given position in file [file:line:character]
  --type-at-pos-batch                                     (mode) show types at multiple positions [file:line:character list]
  --type-error-at-pos                                     (mode) show type error at a given position in file [line:character]
  --is-subtype                                            (mode) take a JSON list of subtype queries via stdin
  --tast-holes                                            (mode) return all TAST Holes in a given file
  --tast-holes-batch                                      (mode) return all TAST Holes for a set of files. Argument is a file containing a newline-separated list of files
  --verbose-on                                            (mode) turn on verbose server log
  --verbose-off                                           (mode) turn off verbose server log
  --version                                               (mode) show version and exit
  -Wall                                                   show all warnings
  -Wnone                                                  hide all warnings
  -W                                                      show all warnings with a given code, e.g. -W 12001
  -Wno                                                    hide all warnings with a given code, e.g. -Wno 12001
  -Wignore-files                                          hide warnings in files matching a regexp
  -Wgenerated                                             show warnings in generated files
  --watchman-debug-logging                                Logs full Watchman requests and responses. This is very noisy
  --ultrahelp                                             see full options (for language and release teams)
  -help                                                   Display this list of options
  --help                                                  Display this list of options
